---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Yoga — Mindful Terms That Score Big"
  description="Yoga and meditation terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. CHAKRA (15pts), MANTRA (8pts), KARMA (11pts). Mindfulness vocabulary for competitive players."
  keywords="scrabble yoga words, chakra scrabble points, mantra scrabble, karma scrabble word, meditation words scrabble, yoga vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Yoga — Mindful Terms That Score Big","description":"Yoga and meditation terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. CHAKRA (15pts), MANTRA (8pts), KARMA (11pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-yoga"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is CHAKRA a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! CHAKRA scores 15 points (C=3, H=4, A=1, K=5, R=1, A=1). The K=5 and H=4 tiles provide the scoring punch. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play KARMA in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. KARMA scores 11 points (K=5, A=1, R=1, M=3, A=1) as a 5-letter word. The K tile alone contributes nearly half the score, making this an efficient short play."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is MANTRA valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! MANTRA scores 8 points (M=3, A=1, N=1, T=1, R=1, A=1). While modest in base value, it uses very common tiles and is easily playable across existing board letters."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Yoga — Mindful Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Sanskrit-origin yoga terms have entered the English lexicon — and the Scrabble dictionary. CHAKRA delivers 15 points by combining C, H, and K tiles, while KARMA uses the high-value K for 11 points in just 5 letters. These mindful words bring inner peace to your rack and outer dominance to the board.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CHAKRA (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KARMA</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MANTRA</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TANTRA</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Enlightened Play</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">CHAKRA — 15 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">C=3, H=4, A=1, K=5, R=1, A=1 · 6 letters · C+H+K power trio</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">An energy centre in the body according to Hindu tradition. CHAKRA delivers 15 points from 6 tiles — 2.5 points per tile. The K=5 provides the core scoring, supported by C=3 and H=4. With two A's and an R as filler, this word is reasonably drawable.</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Core Yoga Terms</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧘 KARMA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · K=5, A=1, R=1, M=3, A=1 · Cosmic cause & effect</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🕉️ MANTRA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · M=3, A=1, N=1, T=1, R=1, A=1 · Sacred chant</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">☮️ TANTRA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · T=1, A=1, N=1, T=1, R=1, A=1 · Spiritual tradition</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪷 NIRVANA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · N=1, I=1, R=1, V=4, A=1, N=1, A=1 · Transcendent state</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Extended Mindfulness Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DHARMA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SUTRA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GURU</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">YOGA</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ASHRAM</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Yoga Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CHAKRA maximises K placement:</span> The K=5 tile is often hard to play. CHAKRA gives it context with common letters (C, H, A, R, A), making it a reliable K-dump word.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">KARMA is a 5-tile efficiency play:</span> At 11 points from 5 tiles (2.2 pts/tile), KARMA outperforms many longer words. It deploys K and M together while using common vowels.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Sanskrit A-heavy words work well:</span> MANTRA, TANTRA, KARMA — these all use multiple A tiles. When you draw 2-3 A's, think Sanskrit before panicking about vowel-heavy racks.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Yoga words are <span class="text-white font-medium">A-heavy and K-friendly</span>. CHAKRA (15pts) and KARMA (11pts) solve two common rack problems: excess A tiles and a stranded K. DHARMA (12pts) adds H into the mix. Memorise these for racks with K+A+A combinations.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-archery/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Archery</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-boxing/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Boxing</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-cycling/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Cycling</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/foreign-words-valid-in-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Foreign Words Valid in Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-k/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words with K</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid yoga word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
